A [[currency_exchange]] with a BTC/USD market for trading between USD (U.S. Dollars) against bitcoins.  The site has Russian and English user interface translations.

The methods allowed for adding funds to an account are [[Liberty_Reserve]], Webmoney WMZ, Interkassa.com and their own BTC-E redeem codes.  The withdrawal methods are Webmoney WMZ, [[Liberty_Reserve]], QIWI, LiqPAY and BTC-E redeem code. BTC-E redeem codes exchange provided by [[AurumXchange]].

Note that BTC-E has been known to freeze accounts and steal their balances from even well-known community members on their own accord, without any judicial authority or basis. Beware.

##History

The site was first announced on July 17, 2011 (2.1) with test mode trading.  Live trading began on August 7, 2011 (2.2).
##Features
###Currency pairs
[BTC-E](http://www.btc-e.com) supports the exchange between the major currency pairs, such as:

* BTC/USD
* SC/BTC, SC/USD
* LTC/BTC, LTC/USD
* RUC/BTC, RUC/USD
* NMC/BTC
###Deposit options

* Liberty Reserve
* Webmoney WMZ 
* Interkassa.com (VISA, MasterCard, PayPal, LiqPay, etc.)
<big>**It's very nice News**</big>: If the amount to deposit more than 30 WMZ - <big>**fee is reduced to 0.08%**</big>. Need sending private messages support, for details..
###Withdraw options
Directly to your e-wallet and the U.S. dollar, such as:

* Webmoney
* Liberty Reserve
* Perfect Money
* LiqPay
* BTC-E code (cash out aurumxchange --> MtGox)
* For (not only) Russian User: АльфаБанк, Телебанк, ПриватБанк, Яндекс.Деньги, RBK Money.
